SUMMARY:Cloud Native Theater | Cloud Native University: How Kubernetes Actually Ships: An Educator's Guide to Core Releases\, SIGs\, and Staying Current - Michael Forrester and Mumshad Mannambeth\, KodeKloud
DESCRIPTION:We're not maintainers. We're not vendors. We're educators who've trained over a million students for CKA\, CKAD\, and CKS—and watched them hit the same wall after passing: "Nobody taught me how to keep up with Kubernetes."\nIn this session\, we'll cover:\n- How Kubernetes core releases work—the 3x/year cadence\, KEPs\, and where the real changelog lives.\n- How SIG projects like Gateway API release independently\, and how to track them.\n- How to navigate GA\, beta\, and alpha—what each stage means and when to care.\n- How to prioritize for your role—operators\, developers\, and architects need different things.\n- Which external sources help and which have an agenda—community resources vs. vendor hype.\nWe've helped more people pass Kubernetes certifications than almost anyone. Now we'll teach you what happens after the exam.
CATEGORIES:SOLUTIONS SHOWCASE
LOCATION:Hall 1-5 | Tram Zone | Cloud Native Theater\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:949a59e8cbd36711db0202ba4536bad7
URL:http://kccnceu2026.sched.com/event/949a59e8cbd36711db0202ba4536bad7
