SUMMARY:Cloud Native Theater | Cloud Native University: The AI-Hiker’s Guide to Cloud Native AI - Cansu Kavili Örnek and Anneli Sara Banderby\, RedHat
DESCRIPTION:The Cloud Native landscape is vast\, and adding Generative AI can make it feel overwhelming for a newcomer. Where do you even start?\n\nThis lightning talk gives first-timers a simple\, practical decision map for the KubeCon week ahead. We will present how AI workloads actually fit into a Kubernetes world\, introducing containers\, how to think about “models as services\,” and what changes when GPUs and latency enter the picture.\n\nWe’ll focus on a simple mental roadmap\, so you can navigate KubeCon sessions with confidence. Start here to get inspiration and learn from people who have tried\, and failed and then succeeded.
CATEGORIES:SOLUTIONS SHOWCASE
LOCATION:Hall 1-5 | Tram Zone | Cloud Native Theater\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
