DTSTART:20260324T123000Z
DTEND:20260324T125000Z
SUMMARY:Sponsored Demo: Autonomous Kubernetes Resource Management in Production
DESCRIPTION:Cost optimization without performance guarantees is gambling with production. In this live demo\, we’ll show how ScaleOps autonomously manages Kubernetes resources in real production clusters\, continuously aligning CPU\, memory\, and replica configurations with actual workload behavior. The goal is simple: every workload runs with exactly the resources it needs. No more. No less. ScaleOps uses context-aware optimization powered by real-time cluster conditions and workload behavior to continuously and autonomously rightsize CPU and memory\, manage replicas\, and eliminate inefficiencies. You’ll see how autonomous actions are validated\, rolled out with guardrails\, and monitored to prevent regression or scaling oscillation across both AI and cloud-native workloads. The result: improved latency and workload stability first\, followed by measurable reductions in overprovisioning and cloud waste\, without manual tuning. If you operate Kubernetes in production and need automation that enforces performance discipline while improving efficiency\, this demo is for you. **In order to facilitate networking and business relationships at the event\, you may choose to visit a third party’s booth or access sponsored content. You are never required to visit third party booths or to access sponsored content. When visiting a booth or participating in sponsored activities\, the third party will receive some of your registration data. This data includes your first name\, last name\, title\, company\, address\, email\, standard demographics questions (i.e. job function\, industry)\, and details about the sponsored content or resources you interacted with. If you choose to interact with a booth or access sponsored content\, you are explicitly consenting to receipt and use of such data by the third-party recipients\, which will be subject to their own privacy policies.**
