SUMMARY:Kubernetes Contribution 101
DESCRIPTION:Want to start contributing to Open Source but have no idea where to begin? It’s common to feel overwhelmed by the scale of these projects or unsure of how to take that first step. Whether you're looking to build your skills\, give back to the community\, or just see how things work behind the scenes\, finding your footing is the hardest part.\n\nIn this session\, we’ll use Kubernetes as our roadmap to show you how a massive project actually functions. We’ll break down how the Kubernetes community is structured\, how the people within it communicate\, and—most importantly—how you can fit in. You’ll learn how to avoid common pitfalls like the 'good first issue' trap and get direct guidance from active contributors on where the best opportunities are hiding. Leave with a clear plan for your first move in the Kubernetes ecosystem.
CATEGORIES:INCLUSION + ACCESSIBILITY
LOCATION:G104 - 105 | Community Hub\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
