SUMMARY:Sponsored Demo: Cherry Picking your Cluster: Building a Modular CaaS with Dell Automation Platform ​
DESCRIPTION:This demo illustrates how the Dell Automation Platform (DAP) empowers architects to build a customized Kubernetes cluster on bare metal in minutes. Moving beyond rigid\, opinionated stacks\, we will show DAP's modular blueprinting approach\, allowing teams to compose exact cluster specifications. Attendees will see how to seamlessly integrate their preferred components\, including networking\, storage\, service mesh\, ingress controllers\, and GPU support\, all with options for air-gapped configurations. The session will feature a live workflow using an AI-assisted editor integrated directly into the IDE\, providing guided help to simplify and standardize blueprint creation. Finally\, we will validate the deployment by rolling out a Grafana workload to prove full end-to-end readiness.\n\n**In order to facilitate networking and business relationships at the event\, you may choose to visit a third party’s booth or access sponsored content. You are never required to visit third party booths or to access sponsored content. When visiting a booth or participating in sponsored activities\, the third party will receive some of your registration data. This data includes your first name\, last name\, title\, company\, address\, email\, standard demographics questions (i.e. job function\, industry)\, and details about the sponsored content or resources you interacted with. If you choose to interact with a booth or access sponsored content\, you are explicitly consenting to receipt and use of such data by the third-party recipients\, which will be subject to their own privacy policies.**
