SUMMARY:Sponsored Demo: Beyond Training: Volcano for Inference & Agents
DESCRIPTION:As AI workloads shift toward massive scale and autonomous agents\, enterprises face a dual challenge: orchestrating complex parallel inference at the bottom\, and meeting the millisecond-latency demands of agents at the top. Volcano is evolving beyond training to bridge this gap via two new sub-projects: Kthena and AgentCube.\n\nThis session demonstrates a complete "Train-Infer-Act" solution. We dive into Kthena\, showcasing its 3-layer architecture (ModelServing -&gt\; ServingGroup -&gt\; Role) that simplifies TP/PP/EP deployments. See how its router leverages KV-cache-aware logic and Prefill-Decode (PD) separation to double throughput.\n\nWe then explore AgentCube\, a Serverless sandbox mechanism for Agent workloads. We’ll demonstrate how "WarmPools" achieve millisecond startup times and how Session-ID routing ensures context persistence. Finally\, we’ll show a live Dify integration\, executing a full-stack AI workflow from intelligent routing to secure code execution.\n\n**In order to facilitate networking and business relationships at the event\, you may choose to visit a third party’s booth or access sponsored content. You are never required to visit third party booths or to access sponsored content. When visiting a booth or participating in sponsored activities\, the third party will receive some of your registration data. This data includes your first name\, last name\, title\, company\, address\, email\, standard demographics questions (i.e. job function\, industry)\, and details about the sponsored content or resources you interacted with. If you choose to interact with a booth or access sponsored content\, you are explicitly consenting to receipt and use of such data by the third-party recipients\, which will be subject to their own privacy policies.**
